provisions.content:
2. In this Order-
      "fluid equivalent volume" means the equivalent volume of fiesh milk
            required to produce one kilogram of a specified dairy product;
      "fresh milk" means milk that has its original qualities,unimpaired;
      "milk fluid equivalent chart" means a chart supplied by the Board to
           guide the conversion of imported quantities of dairy products into
           fluid equivalent volume;
      "specified dairy product" means the dairy products specified in the
           Schedule.,
